      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "This object is expected to be deserialized as hyphen-separated-words, and serialize as camelCaseWords.\nOther words -- AAI provides VID with `workflow-context`, and `new-test-environment.controller.js` expects `workflowContext`.\nThe `Json` word is a workaround for that, as it separates the getter from the getter.\nAnother solution that helps with `hasValidGettersAndSetters()` test is using `@JsonAlias` instead of `@JsonProperty` on the setter.\n\nBTW, I think that maybe this doble-face of the object serialization/deserialization can be unit-tested as well.",
